This paper is about developing a novel approach for dialogue state tracking in spoken dialogue systems. The approach leverages wall-clock temporal difference between turns, which is a key aspect of dialogue scenarios. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with human-computer interaction, which falls under cs.SD (Sound and Dialogue). The paper also involves empirical evaluation, which is a key aspect of cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with spoken dialogue systems, which is a sub-field of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
